ce:section.ce:para:
The effect of possible interference of some species, which could be present in the quercetin measurement process in real samples, was investigated. For this purpose, the experiments were performed by quercetin solution analysis (100 ng mL−1) after adding the different concentrations of interfering species and tolerance limits (interference concentration/ quercetin concentration in ng mL−1) ± 5 % was considered. Based on the results and observations obtained (Table 2
                        ), no substantial interference was apperceived in the quercetin determination process at the declared concentrations. Also, the selectivity of the MIP adsorbent to the structures similar to quercetin (caffeine and gallic acid) and some ions was investigated in the presence and absence of quercetin (100 ng mL−1), which is shown in Fig. 4
                        a. According to the obtained results, there was no significant change in the fluorescence intensity of interfering species in the presence and absence of quercetin. The results show the acceptable selectivity of the Fe3O4@GQDs/MIP adsorbent towards the quercetin molecule, which means that the imprinted sites are spatially compatible with the quercetin molecule and the imprinting process has been performed correctly for quercetin molecule.
